item.title: Agency Services
item.dc:creator: nmsmb
item.content:encoded:
[fullwidth background_class="white spacing intro-lead center" top_border="no" shadow="yes" parallax="no" bottom_margin="yes"]

Why use a DIY tool or cheap vendor, when you can get an Agency for the same price?

We're a full-service Ad Agency, working with some of the largest and best-known brands around. We have developed an effective, proprietary solution to deliver small businesses the same quality and personal attention, at a much lower cost. [columns class="center"] [one_third] [icon name="fa-apple" size="6" color="#bbc0c6" background_color="#fff" circled_background="no"]

iOS Development

Our developers have deployed 500+ iOS apps. We will handle everything for you, from design to development to Apple store submission, with flat fee app pricing starting at $995. [/one_third] [one_third] [icon name="fa-android" size="6" color="#bcdb5c" background_color="#fff" circled_background="no"]

Android Development

Like iOS, our developers have deployed 500+ Android apps, with full-service covering design, development and Google Play submission, and the same flat fee app pricing from $995. [/one_third] [one_third] [icon name="fa-desktop" size="6" color="#67d7ef" background_color="#fff" circled_background="no"]

Website Development

We're experts in the largest CMS tools like Wordpress, Drupal, Joomla, SharePoint, and ExpressionEngine. No matter your needs, we have the team to deliver. From $1,995. [/one_third] [/columns] [columns] [one_third] [icon name="fa-cart-plus" size="6" color="#6edfb6" background_color="#fff" circled_background="no"]

E-Commerce Development

Got products to sell? We offer all the biggest e-commerce tools like Magento, WooCommerce, BigCommerce, and Shopify. Complete E-Store package from $3,995. [/one_third] [one_third] [icon name="fa-eye" size="6" color="#f78774" background_color="#fff" circled_background="no"]

Website/Graphic Design

Our full-service team takes care of this for you too. Just show us sites you like and we'll create a design to meet (or beat) them. This is all included in the fee, with prototypes and iterations, from $1,995. [/one_third] [one_third] [icon name="fa-facebook-square" size="6" color="#3b5998" background_color="#fff" circled_background="no"]

Social Media Management

Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, YouTube and LinkedIn - our social media experts do it all for you! We'll create a page that is all about you, and then help to build your fan base and engage them, from $495. [/one_third] [/columns] [columns] [one_third] [icon name="fa-google" size="6" color="#3f85f4" background_color="#fff" circled_background="no"]

Organic SEO

All sites come with initial SEO in the same low fee. If you want ongoing help, to ensure your site gets ranked highly in the search engines, we can handle that as well! Complete service from just $250/mo. [/one_third] [one_third] [icon name="fa-bar-chart" size="6" color="#70c14a" background_color="#fff" circled_background="no"]

SEM/PPC/Retargeting

Google Adwords, Yahoo and Bing, advertising with tracking pixels, contextual ads, partner publishing - we can help you drive sales using all the best-in-breed tools available today. From just $495. [/one_third] [one_third] [icon name="fa-gear" size="6" color="#b5a8e0" background_color="#fff" circled_background="no"]

Support and Maintenance

Do you already have a website, but need a better partner to manage it? Not getting return calls from your old developer? You just need a reliable team to lean on. One fee, any service: from $60/hour. [/one_third] [/columns] [/fullwidth] [lead_block title="Multiple Industry Solution Experience" text="As a full-service Agency, we've worked with over 600 companies in almost every industry you can imagine. We have the depth and breadth of expertise to deliver for you."][/lead_block] [columns] [one_half] [box_icon_left icon="fa-briefcase" icon_size="2" icon_background="#ccc"]

Business & Finance

We've created online financing applications, banking portals, and numerous B2B sites of all descriptions. [/box_icon_left] [/one_half] [one_half] [box_icon_left icon="fa-shopping-cart" icon_size="2" icon_background="#ccc"]

Consumer & Retail

We've built e-commerce sites to sell everything from home and office furniture to popcorn and snacks to banners and neon signs, including sites that allow you to customize your own t-shirts and clothing. [/box_icon_left] [/one_half] [one_half] [box_icon_left icon="fa-rocket" icon_size="2" icon_background="#ccc"]

Technology

We've developed custom mobile apps to perform a variety of complex functions, written weather prediction software for government agencies, and even a social network ranked higher than Twitter by Mashable.com! [/box_icon_left] [/one_half] [one_half] [box_icon_left icon="fa-plus" icon_size="2" icon_background="#ccc"]

Healthcare

We've created responsive websites for major health insurance groups, mobile apps for use by doctors in the E.R., a portal to allow customers to compare healthcare rates in different markets, and more. [/box_icon_left] [/one_half] [one_half] [box_icon_left icon="fa-play-circle-o" icon_size="2" icon_background="#ccc"]

Media & Entertainment

We've worked with media groups from CBS Television to Bad Boy Entertainment, and created interactive animations for virtual displays, online 3D video to promote the new Ford vehicles, and gaming software for music celebrities. [/box_icon_left] [/one_half] [one_half] [box_icon_left icon="fa-truck" icon_size="2" icon_background="#ccc"]

Transport & Logistics

We've partnered with some of the largest logistics companies in the U.S. to create immersive website experiences and integrate complex software to allow a network of drivers plan effective schedules, while allowing customers to book and track shipments online! [/box_icon_left] [/one_half] [/columns]
[columns class="no-bottom-margin"] [one_third class="no-bottom-margin"]

Benefits of Working With Us

[checklist style="3"]
  • We've delivered over 2000 websites of all shapes and sizes, for huge clients and small businesses.
  • We've been trusted by over 600 companies spanning more than 50 industries.
  • We successfully deliver projects in the $100,000-250,000 range every day. We're talented!
  • But we also deliver high-quality sites for small businesses under $2,000. We're cost-effective!
  • No other company can give you the best of both worlds like we can. And we're nice people!
[/checklist] [/one_third] [one_third class="no-bottom-margin"]

How to Work with Us

[accordions] [accordion title="Step 1: Contact Us Now"] There's no obligation, and we'll provide a free, flat rate 1FEE price to create your site, your app, or anything else you need. [/accordion] [accordion title="Step 2: Project Kickoff"] We'll schedule your project kickoff, where you'll meet your team, to happen as soon as the next day. This can happen in person if you're nearby, or we can use screensharing and videoconferencing software to all be in the same room "virtually." You'll meet your own dedicated Designer, Developer, Project Manager and Project Coordinator. The Project Coordinator is your main day-to-day contact, who you can reach out to for anything you need at any time. They'll work with you to understand your goals, gather requirements and set the project schedule, so you know exactly what to expect from Day One. [/accordion] [accordion title="Step 3: Prototypes"] Your team will create your custom prototypes within 2-5 days. These will include all the design elements, website content, and be fully functional. You will be able to view them on desktop and different mobile devices, to see how the mobile responsiveness works, and test every feature of the site. Don't worry, there's still plenty of time for feedback and iterations, so we can get it just right before we're done. [/accordion] [accordion title="Step 4: Training and Launch"] Once everything looks good and you approve it to go live, we schedule your training. Even though we do everything for you, we want to make sure you know how to use it since this is your site after all. You own it, and we don't want you to feel "locked-in" to us. Training takes about an hour, and we can do it with remote screenshare tools so it doesn't matter where you are. We'll show you how to do everything you can imagine on your site, and we video capture the whole thing you you can re-watch the video whenever you need a refresher. Then it's time to launch, and your new website is visible to the world! [/accordion] [/accordions] [/one_third] [one_third class="no-bottom-margin"]

Why We're Better

We care as much about you and your project as we do every $250,000 client we work with. Our dedicated Agency team will give you full-service, hold your hand every step of the way, and work closely with you as your partner to ensure a fantastic website result! You get the same level of service that bigger clients pay $20,000+ for, but at a cost that is reduced by as much as 90%. We are very efficient, and we give you the best service, combined with the best technology, at a great price. We create it; You own it; All for one flat fee! [/one_third] [/columns] [recent_works title="Featured Projects" number_columns="4" number_posts="8" view_link="yes" view_anchor_text="View" headline="yes"][/recent_works]

item.title: FAQ
item.dc:creator: nmsmb
item.content:encoded:
Can we answer any of your questions?

We offer a complete, all-in-one solution, and as such, want to make sure that you fully understand what we can do, so you can make an apples-to-apples comparison.  We believe you won't find a better product at a better price anywhere.  If the answers below don't give you everything you need, just contact us now and we'll be happy to help! [accordions] [accordion title="Are your websites responsive?"] Absolutely!  Every websote we create is optimized for mobile phones, tablets and desktop monitors.  We even design for super-size monitors (2000px and above) as well as multiple phone sizes (e.g. iPhone 4, iPhone 5 and iPhone 6/6 plus, not to mention all the flavors of Android, Blackberry and Windows Phone). We don't create separate "mobile" versions of your website; we create a single website, fully mobile-responsive, so you only need to manage a single set of content, etc., and you will still get the best results on every device out there.  And it's all included in the price - all for one flat fee. item.title: Clyfford Still Museum
item.dc:creator: nmsmb
item.content:encoded:
[note]Complete Website Design, Custom Web Development, Website Hosting.[/note]
We worked closely with their small, but dedicated, team to design and develop a website that showcased the late artist’s work.
The website needed to be simple and contemporary and with the help of our designers we produced a very clean and easy to use website. We continue work with the museum as they grow, including ongoing consulting and managed web hosting and domain management.
item.excerpt:encoded: With something as large as a new $100 Million museum opened in Denver, solely dedicated to abstract expressionist Clyfford Still, this client knew they needed a company that could provide a complete solution.

item.title: Delta Air Lines
item.dc:creator: nmsmb
item.content:encoded:
[note]Complete Website Design, Custom Web Development, Website Hosting.[/note]
We created the Delta Sky Club portal for Delta Airlines, as the main landing page any passenger would see when they first logged in to use the wi-fi service. Delta wanted a “rich” portal experience, so we created an automated (no manual management required) interactive site to display news, weather, driving directions, track flights, and Google searching - all from one page.
(Note: this website is only available to users within a Delta Sky Club lounge)
item.excerpt:encoded: If you’ve ever flown first class with Delta, or used one of their Sky Club lounges in airports all across the US, you’ve probably seen our work.

item.title: Almond Board
item.dc:creator: nmsmb
item.content:encoded:
[note]Custom Web Development, Content Migration, Infrastructure and Deployment Management.[/note]

The Almond Board needed a website that served both internal and external groups, and did not duplicate content but contained the content of three basically identical sites, and also wanted to be able to appeal to a variety of audiences through design and functionality.

We were able to develop a very complex site using Drupal install profiles that can (among other things) easily accept uploaded CSVs for mass content imports, allowing site management to be much simplified even given the large scope. Since the site has so much content it was also important that the site could be viewed from any device, so it was developed to be fully responsive. Our team kept that in mind with every development decision making sure that the mobile version of ABC would be just as enjoyable (and usable) as the desktop version.
item.excerpt:encoded: The Almond Board of California (www.Almonds.com) is a massive global organization that controls approximately 80% of the world’s almond supply, and they serve several very large, distinct groups of stakeholders.

item.title: Colorado School of Mines
item.dc:creator: nmsmb
item.content:encoded: [note]Complete Website Design, Custom Web Development, Website Hosting.[/note] The new Mines newsroom, newsroom.mines.edu, features news articles, a guide to the world-renowned experts on campus, multimedia content, media mentions, archives and university press releases. We delivered website consulting, website design and Drupal web development services.
item.excerpt:encoded: When world-renowned Engineering University, Colorado School of Mines decided to develop a new online resource to connect journalists and the public with news, events and resources on the university’s campus, they chose us to handle the job

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: This newsroom site will allow us to break stories about Mines and share other news and features showcasing the exciting research and outstanding student experience happening here at Mines

item.title: YMCA
item.dc:creator: nmsmb
item.content:encoded:
[note]Complete Website Design, Custom Web Development, Website Hosting.[/note]
We were able incorporate all of the YMCA's needs and more by using Drupal as a platform. Our team of designers and developers were able to integrate the different branches' locations while maintaining the feel of one site, and the end result went on to be the model for the National YMCA organization YUSA.
item.excerpt:encoded: The team at YMCA (now known simply as the "Y") was looking for a web design team that could showcase their new marketing redesign while maintaining a realistic budget for a non-profit.

item.title: Six Flags
item.dc:creator: nmsmb
item.content:encoded:
[note]Complete Website Design, Custom Web Development, E-Commerce.[/note]
Six Flags came all the way from Texas to work with our team in Denver, CO. The results speak for themselves. Complete website design and Drupal development for Six Flags corporate and 19 individual theme park locations, multiple administrator access levels and e-commerce to process orders for ticket sales and season passes.
item.excerpt:encoded: Complete design and development of Six Flags’ global website, www.SixFlags.com. The site includes their entire corporate public side, a complex back-end intranet for internal resources, and individual sites for their 19 amusement parks across North America.

item.title: University of Colorado
item.dc:creator: nmsmb
item.content:encoded:
[note]Complete Website Design, Custom Web Development, Website Hosting.[/note]
CU initially chose us for the web development side only, choosing to work with a pre-existing vendor relationship to handle the aesthetic considerations, and keep the look and feel consistent with their entire CU brand. However, after the original design vendor couldn't keep up with the requirements, drastically delaying the schedule, and threatening to bring the whole project down before it was even finished, we stepped in to save the day.
We took over the complete website, end-to-end. Our website design team worked with our Drupal developers, start to finish, and completed it in a matter of weeks. The results have been very positively received by everyone from Alumni to Regents, Faculty to prospective students.
item.excerpt:encoded: After the original design vendor couldn't keep up with the requirements, drastically delaying the schedule, and threatening to bring the whole project down before it was even finished, we stepped in to save the day.

item.title: Amtrak Acela
item.dc:creator: nmsmb
item.content:encoded:
[note]Complete Website Design, Custom Web Development, Website Infrastructure Management and Hosting.[/note]
Amtrak Acela services major metropolitan areas during peak commuter hours along the eastern seaboard. Keeping passengers connected with AmtrakConnect Wi-Fi – the Official Wi-Fi is of paramount importance.
We created and managed the wi-fi portal, built and managed their server infrastructure and architected a proprietary ad server model to serve and track all advertising on their Acela train service, supporting about 25,000,000 hits on a monthly basis.
item.excerpt:encoded: When Amtrak began offering free wi-fi on their Acela commuter service, running up and down the east coats, they knew they needed a company that could help build and manage their wi-fi/advertising serving network, and have it scale as they grew their service. They chose us.
